OL,6,FHe continued: "I was delighted when
OL,7,Fthe magistrates said, 'We find you not
OL,8,Fguilty of these charges Mr Stephenson,
OL,9,Fyou're free to leave this court and
OL,10,Falso we're going to offer you 15
OL,11,Fguineas costs against the police for
OL,12,Fbringing this charge in the first
OL,13,Fplace.'
OL,15,F"I thought that was excellent because
OL,16,Fit really did show that the
OL,17,Fmagistrates saw clearly that my case
OL,18,Fwas just and the police and the
OL,19,Flicensee at that time had not got
OL,20,Ftheir facts correct."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
