OL,3,CPub sit-in marks 60 years since one
OL,4,Cman's protest made British history
OL,6,FDr Paul Stephenson, OBE, is a
OL,7,Fcommunity worker, activist, and long-
OL,8,Ftime campaigner for civil rights for
OL,9,Fthe British African-Caribbean
OL,10,Fcommunity in Bristol, England.
OL,12,FAs a young social worker, in April
OL,13,F1963, he led a boycott of the Bristol
OL,14,FOmnibus Company, protesting its
OL,15,Frefusal to employ Black or Asian
OL,16,Fdrivers or conductors.
OL,18,FIn August 1963, the day the Boycott
OL,19,Fdefeated the 'colour bar', Martin
OL,20,FLuther King gave his iconic 'I Have a
OL,21,FDream' speech.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/11
