OL,3,CPub sit-in marks 60 years since one
OL,4,Cman's protest made British history
OL,6,FIn 1964, Paul Stephenson achieved
OL,7,Fnational fame when he refused to leave
OL,8,Fa public house until he was served,
OL,9,Fresulting in a trial for failing to
OL,10,Fleave licensed premises. His campaigns
OL,11,Fwere instrumental in paving the way
OL,12,Ffor the first Race Relations Act in
OL,13,F1965.
OL,15,FBecause of his life's work, in 2007 he
OL,16,Fwas granted the Freedom of The City of
OL,17,FBristol, making him the first Black
OL,18,Fman to become a Freeman of the city.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/11
